Pre-Game Insights: India is flying in the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023 as they have won all their matches played till now in the competition.
They started by beating Australia, but since then they have gathered momentum and went into a winning streak demolishing their oppositions.
India will look to keep their winning streak intact and also rotate some key players.
Netherlands on the other hand have been methodical and impressive in their campaign despite not being familiar with the conditions.
An area they would like to be better ahead of ending their tournament is the batting performing as an unit.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The pitch at the M Chinnaswamy Stadium is hard and the bounce is true with not much assistance for either the seamers of spinners.
Fans can expect a high scoring match again.
There is no forecast of rain during the duration of the match on November 12, 2023.
The temperature is all set to stay between 21-27 degree Celsius.
